    <div class="field field-name-field-ww-summary field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>The common approach these days for storing geolocation data is to use a combination of <a href="http://webwash.net/node/9">Address Field, Geofield, geoPHP and Geocoder</a>. Another way, is to use the good old <a href="http://webwash.net/node/157">Location</a> module.</p>

<p>But, today I want to show you how to use the <a href="https://drupal.org/project/geolocation">Geolocation Field</a> module</p>

<p>The module implements a field that allows you to store longitude and latitude coordinates. But where the module really shines is with its field widgets and formatters.</p>

<p>It ships with two sub-modules called: "Geolocation Google Maps" and "Geolocation HTML5".</p>

<p>The "Geolocation Google Maps" sub-module comes with a pretty cool widget that allows a user to select a location using an address or by clicking on a map. You can select a location by entering in an address and if the location is not right, then just click on the map and fix it up.</p>

<p>The "Geolocation HTML5" sub-module allows you to define your location using <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/geolocation-API/">HTML5's geolocation API</a>.</p>
